<br>
1) Did we ask him to leave ? Yes.  Politely. Several times. His reply ? I will stay until you die or leave.<br>
<br>
2) Yes, we were camping gear for our monk. There are plenty of places where the experience is much better as you don't have such horrid downtime and unknown spawns.<br>
<br>
3) Was the KS &quot;accidental&quot; ? In no way shape or form could it have been accidental. He stood behind us, watching us pull them only to have him nuke it WHILE I was tanking it. Accidental ? Hardly. An &quot;out of control situation&quot; it was clearly not. I was over 80 % health, our rogue was behind it, and a monk nearby to help with melee should I be in danger. <br>
<br>
4) Was this the first occurrence? No. Previously, as I was tanking (weak shaman, working on much needed defense skill ups, so it was taking a bit longer to kill) he pulled one, rooted it, lev'd over water (which, to my knowledge is a known exploit) and killed it.<br>
<br>
5) Yes, he did swim and apparently got his swimming to 158  . (Only mentioned it because mine is barely topping 100 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br>
Yes, Shohgun did use words that I would not have used. However, what our Pizza-named friend failed to mention is that, at some point, he logged off, found our guild web page, looked up Shohgun's email and other personal information, logged back on, and was taunting him with it. Yes, public information, I know, but it was still creepy. <br>
<br>
6) What he also failed to mention is that I spoke with him at length. I wanted to know why he was such a condescending dork, to be honest. I found out that &quot;I don't group&quot; (his exact words, so any chance of him joining us were out) due to &quot;power level reasons&quot; and that &quot;wizards aren't really wanted in groups.&quot; I mentioned that the folks that didn't want wizards, usually aren't aware of their high damage. With his extensive knowledge of the game, apparently there is no place in EQ that he can gate to, solo, and get decent experience at his level. <br>
<br>
7) His AFK tag was on, but he was rarely AFK, judging by the constant remarks and running in and out of the water. <br>
<br>
Do not take us for fools, Froscheto. I understand that &quot;camps&quot; aren't respected by VI, but I do know that for most mature players, they are respected by players. One mob take, after it was obvious we were in your &quot;secret place&quot; shame on me. One KS, shame on me too. Can't blame us for being a little touchy. <br>
<br>
You are an arrogant little gnat, and I'm so glad you felt the need to make this public. Just so you know, we'll leave your &quot;little spot&quot; alone in the future. After a very long stretch with no drops, we decided we'd do better &quot;grouping&quot; in a much better experience place that drops better loot than gator meat and buy the damned things. May you swim and annoy others in peace.<br>
<br>
Dalliance the Shaman<br>
